data.content:
Two files created:

**`SortableList.razor`** — renders a `<ul>` with each item wrapped in a `<li>` containing Move Up/Move Down buttons plus the caller's `ItemTemplate`. Uses `@key` for efficient diffing and disables buttons at list boundaries.

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** — `partial class` with:
- **`Items`** (`IReadOnlyList<TItem>`) — copied into a private `_items` list in `OnParametersSet`, so the parent's collection is never mutated.
- **`ItemTemplate`** (`RenderFragment<TItem>`) — the slot for rendering each item (binds to `@context`).
- **`OnOrderChanged`** (`EventCallback<IReadOnlyList<TItem>>`) — fires after every swap, passing a read-only snapshot of the reordered list.

Usage matches your example:

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskItem> tasks = [ /* ... */ ];

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated)
    {
        tasks = new List<TaskItem>(updated);
    }
}
```
